ment, and shall state such al\nlowance on the proposal form.\nThe Board reserves the right to\nreject any or all bids.\nDelivery of the above named\nequipment must be made within\nseven days after the award to the\nsuccessful bidder.\nAll proposals shall be in writing\nand on the (oi-m prepared for the\nsame, now in the office of the Coun\nty Auditor. and must be filed with\nCounty Auditor, on or before the\nday and hour above mentioned.\nDated this 28th day of September,\n1937. H. E. CHAPMAN.\nCounty Auditor and ex-otficio clerk\nor the Board of Commissioners of\nBenton County, Washington.\nORDINANCE NO. 337\nAn Ordinance Amending Ordinance\nNo. I'l7, being an ordinance en\ntitled \u201cAn ordinance to license and\nregulate certain trades. businesses\nand occupations in the City of\nKennewick, and prescribing pen\nalties for violation and providing\nfor mane:- of eolledztion.\u2019i\nThe City Council of the City of\nKennewick does ordain as follows:\nSection 1. That Ordinance No.\n177 of the City of Kennewick. passed\nJuly 7, 1914, be amended by adding\nthereto a new Section to be known\nas Section 15A as follows:\nSection 15A. In addition to the\ndaily and weekly license fees pro\nvided for in Section 14 and Section\n15 of this Ordinance if any of the\nlicenses required thereunder are de\nsired for a longer period than\none week the person applying for\nthesamemaysecureanannualli\ncense upon payment in advance of\nthe sum of $50.00. Said annual li\ncense shall be for a period coni\nmencing on January 1 of the year\nin which it is issued and the fun li\ncense fee shall be required for any\nperiod less than one year: provid\nedthatanypersondesiringalicense\nhereunder for the period from the\neffective date of this Ordinance to\nJanuary 1 1938 may secure the same\nby paying a fee of $12.50.\"\nSection 2. This Ordinance shall\nbe in effect five days after its ap\nproval, passage and publication in\nthe official newspaper of the City\nof Kennewick.\nPassed October 5, 1